{"id":"ev_e1917c35153a4558","runId":"run_281","type":"delegation","at":1782678517545,"data":{"workItemId":"wi_0316571c324145c4","atom":0,"task":"Author a NEW founder-runnable proof harness `scripts/proof-ticket-close-atomic.mjs` that proves the ticket close lifecycle (defect 7) as ONE command. This is the runnable proof the priority's verification calls for; no current `scripts/proof-*.mjs` covers the close lane.\n\nWHAT TO PROVE (two cases, against the REAL governed close spine — do NOT reimplement close logic):\n1. Status-less atomic close: an open ticket file with NO `status:` frontmatter line, plus an `INDEX.md` row and an `order.json` entry, closes atomically — the file moves to `closed/` with `status: Closed` inserted and a `## Resolution` section appended, `order.json` is pruned of the id, and the `INDEX.md` row is moved to Recently Closed. Assert every surface.\n2. Atomic rollback on forced mid-close failure: force a failure DURING the irreversible mutation phase (e.g. inject a write that throws after the open file is read but before all surfaces are written) and assert ZERO net change remains — open file still present and byte-identical, no `closed/` file, `order.json` unchanged, `INDEX.md` unchanged. Snapshot before/after and compare.\n\nMECHANISM (follow the existing `scripts/proof-*.mjs` convention — see `scripts/proof-governance-authoring.mjs`):\n- Exercise the REAL `closeTicket()` core spine end to end. Because `.mjs` cannot import the `.ts` core directly, drive it through a child process the same way the repo runs TS (the `cocoder` bin registers the tsx ESM loader): spawn `node` with the tsx loader to run a tiny inline/temp TS entry that imports `closeTicket` from `@cocoder/core` and operates on a throwaway temp ticketsDir, OR run the authoritative Vitest close cases (`packages/core/tests/tickets-reconcile.test.ts`) via `--reporter=json` and assert green AND additionally do a live temp-dir close to prove the real file moves. Whichever you choose, the proof must exercise the actual core spine, not a copy of it.\n- Build all fixtures in a fresh temp dir (`mkdtemp` under `os.tmpdir()`). NEVER read or write the real `cocoder/tickets` tree.\n- Always clean up the temp dir (success or failure).\n- Print explicit `PASS: <case>` lines. `process.exit(0)` ONLY if both cases pass; on any assertion failure or unexpected throw print a clear `FAIL: <case> — <why>` and `process.exit(1)`.\n\nACCEPTANCE: `node scripts/proof-ticket-close-atomic.mjs` exits 0 and prints PASS for both the status-less atomic close and the forced-failure zero-state rollback; the forced-failure case asserts the temp fixtures are byte-identical to before.\n\nMUST NOT BREAK: changes confined to `scripts/**` (your only write-scope for this atom). Do NOT edit `packages/core/src/tickets/close.ts` — it is already the correct atomic, status-less-robust implementation; this atom only proves it. Do not touch any real ticket files."}}
